<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Smug" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Smug,</orth> neat, trim, spruce: <cit><quote>used to come so s. upon the mart,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 1, 49</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the s. and silver Trent,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.102" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 1, 102</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I will die bravely, like a s. bridegroom,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.202" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 6, 202</bibl></cit> (Qq <emph>like a bridegroom</emph>).

